   andyweirauthor:

     ANDY WEIR built a career as a software engineer until the success of
     his first published novel, THE MARTIAN, allowed him to live out his
     dream of writing full time. He is a lifelong space nerd and a
     devoted hobbyist of subjects such as relativistic physics, orbital
     mechanics, and the history of manned spaceflight. He also mixes a
     mean cocktail. He lives in California. Moderated by Jason Gessner.
