   Jun 12, 2019

   [anonymous_avatar_96.gif]

   Anonymous asked:

   Is your url a reference to the martian?
   [avatar_6e1b73557466_96.pnj]

   hes-a-steely-eyed-missile-man Answer:

   the fact that someone got the reference pleases me immensely!

   the martian is, of course, one of the greatest books/films to ever have
   been written so kudos to you for having the good taste to have
   seen/read it.

   i actually found out afterwards that ‘steely-eyed-missile-man’ is NASA
   slang term for an astronaut/engineer who comes up with a clever
   solution to a problem under a lot of pressure. apparently it originated
   with John Aaron in the ‘60s: he was on the Apollo 12 mission when it
   was struck by lightning barely 30 seconds after launch. all of the
   telemetry equipment started bugging out however he had seen a similar
   occurence before and advised houston (who had no idea tf he was talking
   about) on what to do, which flipped the readings back to normal again.
   the only reason he knew how to do so was that he had chased up an
   anomaly on telemetry readings on a test at Kennedy a year earlier of
   his own volition. it basically saved apollo 12 and since then he was
   referred to as a ‘steely-eyed-missile-man’.

   it gives a cool little backstory to rich purnell’s assigned nickname in
   the martian so i’d advise you to read the apollo 12 section of Aaron’s
   wikipedia article
     __________________________________________________________________

