   headfulloffantasies: “ Raven’s Reviews Time for another book off my top
   10 list! The Martian by Andy Weir Category: Funniest This book puts the
   science back in science fiction. Astronaut Mark Watney is part of the
   first manned expedition to Mars. A...

   headfulloffantasies:

     Raven’s Reviews
     Time for another book off my top 10 list!
     The Martian by Andy Weir
     Category: Funniest

     This book puts the science back in science fiction. Astronaut Mark
     Watney is part of the first manned expedition to Mars. A massive
     storm forces the team to evacuate. During the evacuation Mark is
     clobbered by flying debris, leading his team to assume he is dead
     and abandon him on Mars.
     Mark faces the monumental task of communicating with earth and
     planning his own rescue, all while dealing with the harsh conditions
     of a literally alien environment.
     I love this book so much. One part survival story, one part science
     fiction, Andy Weir explores human endurance and ingenuity.Mark is a
     clever, hilariously sarcastic narrator who uses black humour to cope
     with his situation. Andy Weir worked with NASA and did the math for
     every scenario Mark goes through. That’s dedication.
     __________________________________________________________________

